Beijing blocks rare earths; the U.S. hits back with 100% tariffs! In three days it went from head-on collision to capitulation, with the CCP forced to “soften up to stop the bleeding,” and the Trump–Xi meeting in Korea proceeding as planned. This isn’t just a cooling of the trade war—it’s a reshuffle of the global chessboard:
 Trump is waging a tariff war in Asia, pushing a peace deal in the Middle East, and geopolitically choking off the Belt and Road. Beijing grabs rare earths; America grabs the entire map.
